President Barack Obama will award Staff Sergeant Ty M. Carter the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan in 2009. Carter, a cavalry scout in the U.S. Army, will be the fifth living recipient of the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He will be honored for his selfless service and bravery. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who display great personal bravery or self-sacrifice in the face of risk to their lives. Each recommendation for the award is considered on the standard of extraordinary merit.